The Federal Government has directed the closure of all offices from 1pm on Tuesday to mobilise support for the Super Eagles against the Black Stars of Ghana in a must-win second leg of the play off for Qatar 2022 World Cup ticket.  The first leg of the play off in Kumasi stadium last Friday ended in a goalless draw with the Eagles needing a win to qualify for the biggest soccer tournament in the world.    Many feared abducted, injured as terrorists attack…     Bandits kill 15 in fresh attack on Kaduna village     I will obey PDP’s decision on zoning- Wike   A statement signed by Dr Ngozi Onwudiwe, Permanent Secretary Welfare Office for the Head of the Civil Service of the Federation, Folasade Yemi-Esan said workers should move to the Moshood Abiola Stadium, Abuja for the match immediately after closure of offices. The statement reads: “As you are aware the Super Eagle of Nigeria will be meeting the Black Stars of Ghana in continuation of the FIFA World Cup qualifier, play off return leg.  ” Consequently, all offices will be closed by 1.pm on Tuesday to enable Nigerians move to the National stadium for the match.”